cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with image classification using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and specifically focuses on modifying the input representation of JPEG compressed data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of ResNet-50 architecture, which falls under the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper proposes a novel approach for modifying the input representation, which involves training CNNs with JPEG compressed DCT coefficients. This falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed approach on public image classification datasets, which falls under the sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper uses the term "efficiency" to describe the performance of the proposed approach, which suggests that it may fall under the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
